The V06 fix is iterating solcInput.sources entries but the SolcInputSource type doesn't have `content`. Per solc-js standard input JSON, sources can be either `{ content: string }` OR `{ urls: string[] }`. The narrow type used here probably only allows the urls variant or doesn't unify with content.

Fix:
- Open both files (writeArtifacts.js, writeArtifactsSync.js) and look at the destructure.
- Either (a) JSDoc-cast the entry to a union that includes `{ content?: string }`, or (b) check whether `content` exists before reading, or (c) update the JSDoc type annotation for the parameter to use a more accurate union.

